title: DIARY- Emerging Markets Economic Events to Sept 9
text:
Aug 28 (Reuters) -
For other diaries, please see:
Top economic events
Government debt auctions
Political and general news events
Index of all diaries
Guide to economic indicators
** This Diary is filed daily ***
FRIDAY, AUGUST 28 SANTIAGO - Central bank of Chile will publish the minutes of August interest rate meeting - 1130 GMT.
TUESDAY, SEPTEMBER 1
JAKARTA - IMF Managing Director Christine Lagarde visits Indonesia (to Sept. 2). SANTIAGO - Central bank of Chile will release quarterly Monetary Policy Report - 1400 GMT. BRASILIA - Brazilian central bank holds monetary policy committee meeting (to Sept. 2). WARSAW - National Bank of Poland holds Monetary Policy Council meeting (to Sept. 2). WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 2 JAKARTA - Conference on "Future of Asian financing" in Indonesia. Speakers:- IMF Managing Director Christine Lagarde, Reserve Bank of India Deputy Governor Urjit Patel, Bank of Japan Deputy Governor Hiroshi Nakaso, Indonesia Finance Minister Bambang Brodjonegoro and IMF Monetary and Capital Markets Department Division Chief Ulric Erickson von Allmen. BANGKOK - International Monetary Fund Managing Director Christine Lagarde visits Indonesia. JAKARTA - IMF Managing Director Christine Lagarde holds press conference - 0915 GMT. WARSAW - National Bank of Poland announces rate decision - 0930 GMT. BRASILIA - Brazilian central bank announces rate decision - 2200 GMT. KUALA LUMPUR - Central bank of Malaysia holds Monetary Policy Committee meeting (to Sept. 3).
THURSDAY, SEPTEMBER 3 KUALA LUMPUR - Central bank of Malaysia announces interest rate decision - 1000 GMT.
FRIDAY, SEPTEMBER 4
TOKYO - International Monetary Fund Deputy Director (Asia and Pacific Department) Kalpana Kochhar speaks at the IMF seminar - Reloading Abenomics: Priorities for the Needed Regime Shift - 0600 GMT. ANKARA - G20 Finance Ministers and Central Bank Governors meeting (to Sept. 5).
MONDAY, SEPTEMBER 7 ISTANBUL, Turkey - Young Businessmen Association of Turkey (TUGIAD) hosts Young Entrepreneurs' Alliance (YEA), part of G20 summit (to Sept. 9).
WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 9
BUDAPEST - Central bank of Hungary to publish the minutes of August rate meeting - 1200 GMT.
